-- Apple CEO says product innovation remains priority
-- 
-- Mon Mar 19, 2012 10:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/03/19/us-apple-ceo-idUSBRE82I0HB20120319

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Apple Inc Chief Executive Officer Tim Cook promised on Monday to periodically review the company's dividend and share repurchase plans but his priority remains product innovation. 
 In a rare non-earnings teleconference, the CEO who replaced Steve Jobs after the iconic co-founder died in October told analysts the company had a "record" weekend for iPad sales, without elaborating. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta  and  Edwin Chan ; Editing by Gerald E. McCormick)